<HEADLINE> WBA Annual Meeting Opens In Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The World Boxing Association
(WBA) opened its 77th annual meeting here Wednesday to review the
organization's performances last year.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 representatives from 147 countries and regions
are attending the conference which will discuss the WBA's
regulations, and performances of referees, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Former WBA champion boxers from Thailand, Khaosai Galaxy and
Saen Sor Plernchit, will receive a special prize during the
meeting which will be presided over by WBA president Guilberto
Mendoza.
</P>
<P>
Mendoza said at the opening ceremony that the meeting will
work out measures to ensure the continuity of WBA's regulations
and create what it lacks in terms of regularities.
</P>
<P>
Boxing, he said, must conform with the drastic changes of the
world and the WBA should meet the challenges of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Among the well-known figures attending the conference will be
promoter Bob Arum.
</P>
<P>
As part of the conference program, Thai Ratanapol Vorapin is
set to sign a contract on Thursday to fight Will Grigsby in the
United States for the IBF flyweight title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
