<HEADLINE> Italian Manufacturers Express Confidence in Textile Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Italian textile machinery
manufacturers continue to express their confidence in the China
market even though related export to the country dropped 40
percent for the first five months this year, according to an
unnamed Italian trade official.
</P>
<P>
The Italian Pavilion features 100 exhibitors, the largest
foreign delegation attending the '98 China International Textile
Machinery Exhibition, which opened on October 13.
</P>
<P>
The Italian textile machinery industry ranks second in the
world in terms of and is the leading supplier of related products
to China. The 1997 textile machinery import volume for Italian
products hit 272 million US dollars, or some 14.7 percent of the
nationwide total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
