<HEADLINE> Makinen Keeps Alive Hope For Another World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Tommi Makinen drove his
Mitsubishi to a narrow victory Wednesday in the San Remo Rally,
keeping himself on route to a repeat world title.
</P>
<P>
The Finn saw his comfortable time advantage shrink at the
third leg but he held on to beat runner-up Piero Liatti, an
Italian with the Subaru team, by 15.08 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Makinen's time for the three legs totalled 4 hours, 34
minutes, 34.5 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The victory, worth 10 points in the season standings, gave
him 48, just two behind leader Carlos Sainz of Spain.
</P>
<P>
The Toyota driver finished fourth in San Remo, 1:31.9 off the
pace. He was just 1.7 seconds behind third-place finisher Colin
McRae.
</P>
<P>
There are two rallies left on 13-event calendar including the
Australia event from November 5-8 and Britain's RAC from
November 21-24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
