<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 16:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Nicosia House Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- A 19th century house built in
Nicosia over tombs dating to the Hellenistic age were awarded
Wednesday an Europa Nostra award for their renovation and
preservation work.
</P>
<P>
The two-story house, which is situated in the old and
picturesques neighborhood Ayioi Omologites of Nicosia, was chosen
among 150 applications from 21 countries.
</P>
<P>
The four ancient tombs, which are in the house, in the verandah
area and in the garden, were found during the renovation
and restoration work and have been well preserved.
</P>
<P>
The house was given the award for the good preservation work,
with the use of traditional materials, methods and constructural
details.
</P>
<P>
According to Europa Nostra, the preservation of the four tombs
is an excellent example of how archaeological sites in private
property can be preserved.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus' Antiquities Department believes the tombs in the house
are part of the Ayioi Omoligites ancient necropolis dating to the
Hellenistic period (323-58 B.C.).
</P>
<P>
Europa Nostra, a pan-European organization whose network
comprises over 200 non-governmental organizations in the field of
conservation, aims at the protection and enhancement of the
architectural and natural heritage, the encouragement of high
standards of architecture and the improvement of the environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981015.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-14 16:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus' Exports Decreases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' export volume in the
first seven months of this year decreased by 1.84 percent,
compared to that of the same period last year, resulting in a
slight increase of trade deficit by 0.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
A foreign trade statistics report, released here by the
Department of Statistics and Research Wednesday, said total
exports in this period were 364.9 million pounds (729.8 million
U.S. dollars) compared to 371.6 million pounds (743.2 million
dollars) in January-July 1997.
</P>
<P>
The imports totaled 1,109.5 million Cyprus pounds (2,219 million
dollars), compared with 1,113.8 million pounds (2227.6 million
dollars) in the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the above developments, the trade deficit
totaled 744.5 million pounds (1,489 million dollars), 2.3 million
pounds (4.6 million dollars) more than that in the first seven
months of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The report said the European Union (EU) countries' exports to
Cyprus accounted for 53 percent of Cyprus' total imports,
compared with 46.9 percent during January-July 1997.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the EU countries imported 57.4 percent of Cyprus'
exports, followed by the Arab countries with a share of 23.7
percent. The corresponding shares of the EU countries and the Arab
countries for January-July 1997 were 51.2 percent and 27.1 percent
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
