of Women Entrepreneurs (AFWE) Secretary General who is already in
Addis Ababa, as saying that the numerous conflicts and natural
disasters are holding back development by keeping the investors
away, thereby giving Africa a negative image of high risk
continent.
</P>
<P>
Quachey said that the only way to make Africa attractive is by
bringing peace, stability and developed infrastructure. She
appealed to African governments to have the political will to
address these problems.
</P>
<P>
AFWE was created in 1993 in Accra, Ghana through the
initiative of the United Nations Economic Commission for Africa
(ECA).
</P>
<P>
The First Global Women Entrepreneurs Trade Fair took place in
Ghana in 1996. 
