<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Sharply on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices plunged on
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as the benchmark Straits Times
Index (STI) lost 29.86 points to end at 985.78 points, dropping
again below the 1,000-point level.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 310.37 million units valued at 282.63
million Singapore dollars (about 173.39 million U.S. dollars).
There were 171 gainers against 87 losers with 162 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Van DH was the most actively traded stock of the day as it had
a volume of 21.23 million units traded. Uraco was the second most
active stock with a turnover of 17.63 million units. Heshe was
third with 16.30 million counters changing hands.
</P>
