Transmarco led the ascent of the day with a rise of 74 cents to
3.46 Singapore dollars at close. Acma moved up 20.5 cents to end
at 0.74 Singapore dollars. Robinson was up 12 cents to end at 3.98
 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH was the biggest loser of the day as it
lost 1.20 Singapore dollars to close at 13.70 Singapore dollars.
Creative 50 slid 80 cents to 15.60 Singapore dollars. Hiap Moh
shed off 45 cents to end at 0.45 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed Wednesday's decline to the fall of property
and banking stocks. 
