<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China on Outer Space Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Conference on
Disarmament should work toward negotiating a treaty on the
prevention of weaponization of outer space, China's representative
said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Li Changhe for Disarmament Affairs made the remarks
at the First Committee of the 53rd Session of the U.N. General
Assembly. He noted that the activities in developing and testing
outer space weapons systems have intensified in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Some of the systems are entirely deployed in outer space or
targeted at objects in outer space, and others are based in outer
space to provide target information or guidance for ground weapon
systems, he said.
</P>
<P>
"As a consequence of such activities, outer space will be
turned into a weapon base and battle field, and regional and
global strategic stability will be undermined," Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that the Conference on Disarmament, the single
multilateral disarmament negotiating forum, re-establish the Ad
Hoc Committee to negotiate a treaty on the prevention of
weaponization of outer space to complement the existing legal
instruments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
