<DOCNO> XIE19981015.0040 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tang Shubei Urges End to Cross-Straits Hostilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Tang Shubei, executive vice
president of the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan
Strait (ARATS), today called for an end of the state of
cross-Straits hostilities.
</P>
<P>
Tang stressed that ending hostilities is not only the will of
people on both sides of the Straits, but also represents their due
right.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remarks during a press conference following a
meeting between ARATS President Wang Daohan and his Taiwan
counterpart Koo Chen-fu, chairman of the Straits Exchange
Foundation (SEF).
</P>
<P>
He said putting an end to cross-Straits hostilities is the
common aspiration of 1.2 billion Chinese citizens and compatriots
in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He also called for the direct cross-Straits mail, commercial
and transportation links, and said the indirect exchanges not only
harm the interests of Taiwan compatriots and but are also the root
cause of disputes.
</P>
<P>
Tang stressed that the Chinese mainland has consistently
attempted to maintain and guarantee the practical interests of
compatriots on both sides of the Taiwan Straits. He said the
effort includes protecting the livelihood and property of three
million Taiwan compatriots who operate business ventures, as well
as those who visit friends or relatives, and others who purchase
homes on the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Frequent personnel exchanges across the Taiwan Straits have
unfortunately resulted in inevitable incidents involving the
infringements on both the life and property of Taiwan compatriots,
said Tang.
</P>
<P>
He said that law enforcement departments on either side of the
Straits can readily solve related cases by improving security, and
noted that ARTS and SEF should expand cooperation in order to
provide mutual assistance when necessary.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that concerned departments on the mainland will
continue to attach great importance to matters involving the life
and property of Chinese citizens on both sides of the Straits.
</P>
<P>
ARATS will continue to offer all possible assistance to SEF in
order to maintain legitimate rights and interests of compatriots
on both sides of the Taiwan Straits, said Tang.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
