<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ARATS, SEF Leaders Hold Candid Dialogue (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Wang Daohan, president of the
Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Strait (ARATS), said
here today that the official end of the state of hostility across
the Taiwan Straits under the one-China principle is an essential
step for the further growth of the cross-straits relations.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that ending the state of hostility complies with the
interests of the people across the Taiwan Straits as well as
Taiwan compatriots' desire for stability and peace.
</P>
<P>
Wang made the remark during his meeting with Koo Chen-fu,
chairman of the Taiwan-based Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF),
here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
During the one-hour meeting, they held a candid dialogue on a
series of questions across the straits including political issues
in a calm atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing after the meeting, Tang Shubei, executive
vice-president of the ARATS, said that Wang Daohan suggested
holding various dialogues between the ARATS and SEF for the
benefits of the peaceful reunification of China and the
development.
</P>
<P>
If the Taiwan side has some difficulties in holding talks on
procedural matters for political negotiation, the ARATS suggests
holding dialogues with the SEF, Wang said, adding that such
dialogues also include political ones, since it is difficult for
the two sides to shun political dialogue while holding dialogues.
</P>
<P>
The suggestion is positive as it has taken into account the
stance of both sides and it is aimed at promoting the relations
across the Straits, he added.
</P>
<P>
Wang went on to say that it has fully give expression to the
sincerity and efforts of the mainland for seeking common ground
while reserving differences and re-opening negotiations between
the two sides across the Straits.
</P>
<P>
He noted that promoting political negotiations across the Taiwan
Straits serves as a key to improving cross-Straits relations at
the current times.
</P>
<P>
"It is our persistent position that under the precondition of
one China, the two sides can hold talks on whatever
subjects. Mr. Jiang Zemin has proposed that the first step for the
two sides is to hold negotiations and reach consensus "under
one-China principle and formerly end the state of hostility across
the Taiwan Straits."
</P>
<P>
On this basis, Wang noted, the two sides jointly make
commitment to safeguarding the motherland's sovereignty and
territorial integrity as well as making plans for the development
of the relations across the Straits.
</P>
</TEXT>
