<HEADLINE> ARATS, SEF Leaders Hold Candid Dialogue (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wang said that at present preparations for political
negotiations across the straits and procedural arrangement for the
negotiations are expected to be made.
</P>
<P>
Through the talks on procedural matters, both sides can reach
consensus on the topics of the political talks, and under what
name and in what way the delegates are going to hold talks, he
said.
</P>
<P>
With this channel and mechanism, the Taiwan side can raise
other questions it is concerned with for further discussion, Wang
said.
</P>
<P>
He held that the talks between the ARATS and SEF should serve
to develop the relations across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Now the situation has undergone great changes and the talks
across the straits are expected to add new contents, he said.
</P>
<P>
What hindered the progress in the talks between the ARATS and
SEF in the past was attributed to the absence of conditions for
discussing such topics that involved political issues, he noted.
</P>
<P>
As a matter of fact, he added, procedural topics cannot be
separated from political issues. It is unfavorable for the
settlement of issues and for the growth of relations across the
straits if talks on political issues are shunned or are limited to
practical issues. So political negotiations have objectively been
put on the agenda.
</P>
<P>
Wang stressed that "the realization of the negotiations across
the straits will create still better conditions for providing the
settlement of economic issues between the two sides. I am willing
to reaffirm that after the talks on procedural matters of the
political negotiations begin, the ARATS and SEF can re-start their
talks on economic and practical issues."
</P>
<P>
Tang Shubei said that Koo Chen-fu also voiced his opinions on
holding dialogues or "constructive" dialogues across the straits.
</P>
<P>
Although they used somewhat different terms, they shared a view
on holding dialogues between the two sides including political
ones, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the meeting the two leaders also had a
frank exchange of ideas on some political issues including the
establishment of mutual trust and ending the state of hostility,
safeguarding the legal rights and interests of the compatriots
across the Straits.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will meet again tomorrow to confer on the
issues of mutual interest and individual concern. 
</P>
