<HEADLINE> U.S. Grants $23.4m to Ethiopia's Education, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia and the U.S.
Wednesday signed here two grant agreements amounting to 23.4
million U.S. Dollars to support health and education projects in
Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Ethiopian News Agency said that the 11.4
million Dollars will be used to support the health sector
development program while the remaining 12 million Dollars will
go to the educational sector development program.
</P>
<P>
The agreement on the education sector is part of the on-going
basic education system overhaul program, which is an 80 million
Dollar bilateral program providing technical assistance, training
and commodities to the education sector.
</P>
<P>
The agreement on the health sector is part of the program for
essential health services in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the allocation for the education and
health projects by U.S. is 136.5 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
So far, 98 milion Dollars have been realeased for the
implementation of the stated projects, of which 54.5 million
Dollars were disbursed for basic education system overhaul, and
the rest of 43.5 million were for health services in the country.
