outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK), has left Syria, the
spokesman said, "it has to be confirmed."
</P>
<P>
"We need confirmation on whether or not Ocalan is out of
Syria," Atacanli said.
</P>
<P>
There are reports that Ocalan has left Syria which Turkey
accuses of supporting the Kurdish rebels fighting against the
Turkish government in southeastern Turkey, amid recent
Turco-Syrian tension.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with a Kuwaiti daily, Syrian Information
Minister Mohammad Salman even said that the PKK leader had not
been in Syria for the past three months.
</P>
<P>
"If Syria really wishes to end the tension or prevent that
tension from taking different dimensions, it should cease
supporting the terrorist organization," Atacanli said.
</P>
<P>
Angered by the alleged Syria's support to the PKK, Turkey has
sounded a serious warning against Damascus that Turkey has run out
of its patience over this issue.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the Turkish parliament early last week, Turkish
Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz stated that Turkey has to make
necessary preparations for a war against Syria if the Arab
country continues supporting the PKK.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian administration softened its attitude following
Turkey's military warning and signaled a message, conveyed to
Ankara by Egypt, that it would reconsider its policies on this
issue. 
