<HEADLINE> Negotiators Reach Consensus on Cross-Straits Relations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Leaders from the Association
for Relations Across the Taiwan Strait (ARATS) and Taiwan-based
Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) today reached a consensus of
four points involving dialog on political and economic issues.
</P>
<P>
ARATS President Wang Daohan and SEF Chairman Koo Chen-fu
exchanged the following views in an unconstrained atmosphere:
</P>
<P>
-- The leaders decided that the two side should continue dialog
on various subjects involving political and economic
issues. Detailed arrangements for related talks will be determined
later by leaders of the two organizations;
</P>
<P>
-- The two sides will increase exchanges between leaders at all
levels, including members of their respective boards of directors,
supervisors and advisors, members of executive councils, and
deputy secretary-generals.
</P>
<P>
-- ARATS and SEF also plan to increase coordination related to
individual cases of the livelihood, property and security of
compatriots from both the mainland and Taiwan. The two sides will
provide mutual assistance needed to deal with particular cases.
</P>
<P>
-- Wang expressed gratitude and accepted Koo's invitation to
visit Taiwan. Wang said he will visit at an appropriate time and
expressed willingness to acquaint himself more with how things are
like in Taiwan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
