<HEADLINE> Negotiators Reach Consensus on Cross-Straits Relations (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ARATS Executive Vice-President Tang Shubei and SEF
Vice-Chairman and Secretary-General Shi Hwei-yow attended an
afternoon press conference and gave a briefing on Wang-Koo Meeting.
</P>
<P>
In reply to a reporter's question on Wang's upcoming visit to
Taiwan, Tang said he thinks it would be a bit hasty for Wang to
visit Taiwan within the year.
</P>
<P>
Tang then recounted that the ARATS invitation for Koo to visit
the mainland was finalized in several months. "I think it
represents a good start," said Tang when referring to the
four-point consensus reached by both sides.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the two sides engage in mutual efforts and
reach an even great consensus prior to Wang's visit to Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question concerning the resumption of dialog
between ARATS and SEF, Tang cited an agreement he reached with Shi
Hwei-yow calling for joint efforts be made to create conditions
and explore opportunities for the resumption of talks between
the ARATS and SEF.
</P>
<P>
The ARATS and SEF have followed various models and conventional
practices when handling unexpected incidents, Tang said. They will
inform each other of incidents and ensure that related departments
handle cases in a timely and effective manner.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the ARATS and SEF have adopted close contacts and
entrustment approaches to provide mutual assistance, and the
practice fully complies with the current state of the development
of cross-Straits relations, Tang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
