<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Attention Urged for African Women's Participation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Second Global Women
Entrepreneurs Trade Fair was opened here Thursday by
Ethiopian President Negasso Gidada, urging more attention to
women's role in economic development.
</P>
<P>
In his keynote address at the opening ceremony, Negasso said:
"Over the last many years experiences have taught us a good
lesson about the need to pay more attention to the role of
African women in Africa's economic development."
</P>
<P>
"If women who constitute more than 50 percent of the population
of Africa are hindered in their ability to achieve economic autonomy
and ensure sustainable livelihood for themselves and their
dependents, then Africa's economic development will continue to be
bleak," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The President called for ways to ensure equality between men and
women in economic, social and political fields, saying that "men and
women need to join together in new partnership and forge alliance
for an equitable development of the continent."
</P>
<P>
Salim Ahmed Salim, Secretary General of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU), expressed at the ceremony that the
organization's support for African women to hold trade fair,
saying that this is "a demonstration of African women
entrepreneurs to play prominent role in Africa's economic
development."
</P>
<P>
The theme of the trade fair is "credit and direct
investment for the enhancement of women entrepreneurs
participation in the global economic recovery and development in
Africa".
</P>
<P>
The Second Global Women Entrepreneurs Trade Fair is a
follow-up of the First Global Women Entrepreneurs Trade Fair
which was held in Accra, Ghana in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The nine-day trade fair, which will include conferences and
workshops, is expected to attract over 1,000 participants from
more than 60 countries around the world and over 1,000 women from
Ethiopia alone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981015.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Motorcycle Fair Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Autumn China
Motorcycle and Accessories Trade Fair closed today in Jinhua, east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
