<HEADLINE> Mubarak Meets With Jordanian PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
Thursday met with Jordanian Prime Minister Fayez Tarawneh, who
arrived here earlier in the day with a message from Jordanian
Crown Prince Hassan, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The message deals with the outcome of Hassan's recent talks
with Palestinian President Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, and the latest developments in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal el-Ganzouri, Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa and his Jordanian counterpart Abdul Ilah al-Khatib, as well
as Jordanian Ambassador to Egypt Torad el-Fayez attended the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tarawneh later held talks with el-Ganzouri on bilateral
relations and efforts exerted to propel the peace process in the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Jordan are the only Arab countries that have peace
agreements with Israel and have played important roles in the
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Tarawneh, who came for a few-hour lightning visit to Egypt,
said his trip fell within the context of close coordination
between Jordan and Egypt over issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's ambassador, who attended the meeting, described his
country's relations with Egypt as excellent at all levels and paid
tribute to bilateral cooperation in all spheres.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Egyptian-Jordanian Higher Joint Committee
will convene in Amman next month. 
