<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Leaves for Beijing to Make Duty Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has undergone great
changes both politically and economically since its return to the
motherland in July last year, said Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a press conference here on Thursday
before leaving for a second duty visit to Beijing. Tung made his
first duty visit last December.
</P>
<P>
Politically, Hong Kong has changed from a territory under
colonial rule into a highly-autonomous SAR where the concepts of
"One Country, Two Systems" are being implemented, Tung said. And
the serious efforts made by China's central government in the
implementation of the concepts had been recognized worldwide. This
is a great achievement scored by the central government and the
6.5 million people of Hong Kong SAR, he stated.
</P>
<P>
Economically, although Hong Kong is facing a tough challenge
brought about by the regional financial crises, the SAR government
has made great efforts for economic recovery and in this respect
we now have a clear-cut orientation, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"We have a very good economic foundation and therefor there is
a good chance for a steady recovery of our economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
And the most important thing for the people of Hong Kong is
that they must be confident of themselves so that the economy
could recover soon, he added. 
</P>
