<HEADLINE> Macao Security Secretary Returns from Beijing Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A senior security official of
Macao said here Thursday evening that police authorities in Macao
and Beijing have agreed to strengthen cooperation in the crackdown
on organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
Brigadeiro M. Monge, Macao government's secretary for security,
made the remark at the Macao International Airport on returning
from his one-week visit to the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, he met with Jia Chunwang, minister of public
security, and Chen Ziying, secretary-general of the Preparatory
Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese officials pay much attention to the public security
affairs in Macao, said Monge, who in turn talked about the
endeavor of the Macao government to crack down on crimes,
especially on trans-border crimes and organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will take measures to enhance the contact of
security officials and information exchange between the security
authority of Macao and those in Beijing, Guangzhou and Zhuhai,
Monge said.
</P>
<P>
The secretary noted that the effect of fighting against crimes
depends on the close cooperation of security authorities near
Macao.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Entao, assistant minister of public security of China,
has agreed to visit Macao by the end of the year, he said.
</P>
