<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Important for EU, says EC Ambassador in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The ever first visit by the
president of the European Commission (EC) to Hong Kong early next
month demonstrates that the European Union (EU) attaches great
importance to the city, the EU ambassador in Hong Kong said here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Etienne Reuter, head of the Office of the European Commission
in Hong Kong, told reporters Thursday afternoon that a delegation
led by the EC President Jacques Santer and Vice President Leon
Brittan will pay a visit to Hong Kong between November 2-3 as part
of their trip to China.
</P>
<P>
The delegation of the EC, executive body of the EU, will
comprise EC officials and a number of European businessmen. They
are scheduled to arrive in China on October 29 and will come to
Hong Kong after their visits to Beijing and Shanghai, Reuter said.
</P>
<P>
Their visit to Hong Kong will also coincide with the second
meeting of the EU-Hong Kong Business Cooperation Council, which
was established in October last year when Chief Executive Tung
Chee Hwa of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
visited the EC. The first meeting of the council was held last
year in Brussels, where the EU headquarters is located.
</P>
<P>
This is the first visit by an EC president to China since 1985
and the first visit by an EC president ever to HK, Reuter said.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day visit to Hong Kong, Santer and Brittan will
meet HKSAR officials, members of the Legislative Council and
business leaders to talk about political as well as economic
issues including the Asian financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Reuter said that the delegation will convey three messages to
Hong Kong. The first is to congratulate Hong Kong on its smooth
reunification with China, Reuter said.
</P>
<P>
The second is that the EC understand the HKSAR's measures to
intervene in the stock and futures markets in Hong Kong and the EC
is convinced that Hong Kong remains an open and free market.
</P>
<P>
The third message is that EC will seek ways to strengthen the
cooperation between Hong Kong and the EU.
</P>
<P>
Reuter said that Hong Kong is very important to European
countries as a bridge between China and Europe and a business hub
to Asia. There are more than 50,000 EU citizens and some 600
EU-based companies in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
