<HEADLINE> Rockets Hit Northern Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Rockets hit villages in
northern Israel Thursday, without causing casualties, Israel Radio
quoted army sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The rockets, which were fired from south Lebanon, landed at the
villages in the West Galilee area, damaging properties there, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese Hezbollah, or Party of God, has claimed
responsibility for the attack. But it did not give the reasons.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah is leading a war of attrition against Israel in south
Lebanon, where the Jewish state set up a self-styled security zone
to allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border attacks
by Lebanon's Muslim guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Under a ceasefire agreement signed in 1996, Israel and Lebanon
agreed not to attack each other's civilian targets in any military
operations. 
