<HEADLINE> Chinese Forest Parks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China has 874 forest parks on a
total of 7.48 million hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-eight of those parks cover more than 10,000 hectares
each and separate coverage of five parks reaches more than 100,000
hectares, according Sun Gang, deputy director of the China
National Tourism Administration.
</P>
<P>
Forest tourism has developed rapidly since the first
State-level forest park was built in Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province,
in 1982, Sun says. The forest parks have had more than 50
million tourists annually in recent years. From 1992 to 1997,
earnings from forest parks amounted to more than 2 billion yuan,
and nearly 100,000 farmers got away from poverty in this way.
</P>
<P>
China has put more than a billion yuan into improving scenic
spots and services in the forest parks in the past decade.
</P>
<P>
Sun says that developing forest tourism will be a key project
for the '99 China Ecological Tourism Year. A Forestry Ministry
plan calls for 2,000 forest parks by the year 2010, on 19 million
hectares of land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
