<HEADLINE> Somali Faction Clashes With Businessmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A new wave of armed
confrontations began Thursday between militiamen loyal to faction
leader Oman Ali Atto and others loyal to a group of businessmen
at the strong point K-7 in south Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said that the clashes began after a convoy of
lorries transporting sugar and other goods from the natural port
of Merca, 100 km south of Mogadishu, and several battle wagons
escorting thm have tried to pass the roadblock where extortion
money is usually solicited by Osman Atto's men manning the
roadblock.
</P>
<P>
At least six people have died including two children who died
in their house not very far away from the area when a stray
round of anti-aircraft rocket hit their house.
</P>
<P>
More than 10 others are believed to have been wounded.
</P>
<P>
The eyewitnesses also reported that nearly 10 lorries carrying
sugar still remain blocked in between the combatant militiamen at
the K-7 junction each side trying to take them.
</P>
<P>
Each side is trying to call for a reinforcement militiamen and
extra battle wagons. At the time being 22 battle wagons are
engaged in this confrontation while many more are expected to
join them especially from the side of the businessmen who now
seem to have committed in their fight against the illegal
roadblocks.
</P>
<P>
Osman Atto's men have been forced to retreat back to the
university compound from where they are still shelling the
advancing businessmen's fighters and their convey.  
</P>
