<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Regional Environmental Protection Cooperation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
However, Li said, the Chinese government is aware of the fact
that the environmental situation is still "very grim" and the
country faces an immense amount of work in protecting the
environment, bit it is confident that it can solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
This morning, NPC Standing Committee Vice-chairman Zou Jiahua
asked the international community to develop policies that will
ensure the development of tourism.
</P>
<P>
Pete Hodgson, acting chairman of the conference's executive
committee, said it has become a commonplace that environmental
protection should be placed before development. He expressed
appreciations for the preparations and arrangements China has made
for the conference and said he hopes to acquire a better
understanding of China's efforts and achievements in environmental
protection at the conference.
</P>
<P>
Qu Geping, chairman of the conference and head of the Chinese
delegation, presided over today's session.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng and his wife Zhu Lin met with leaders of various
countries' delegations and their spouses this evening and later Li
hosted a reception in honor of all participants in the conference.
</P>
<P>
More than 160 delegates from 27 countries and international
organizations attended the conference which will last through
October 18. 
