<DOCNO> XIE19981015.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in S.Korea Begins Gaining Vitality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Foreign direct investment in
South Korea amounted to 532 million U.S. dollars in September, up
30.7 percent from the previous month's 407 million dollars, the
Ministry of Finance and Economy said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The investment growth also represented an increase of 22.6
percent from 434 million dollars in the same period last year, the
ministry said through a spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign investment in Korea began picking up again last month
after suffering a setback in August due to seasonal factors and
the spread of international financial jitters," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In the year's first four months, foreign investment remained in
the doldrums as foreign confidence in the crisis-stricken South
Korean economy sank, but it began picking up in May due to the
implementation of far-reaching restructuring measures.
</P>
<P>
However, in August, foreign capital inflow plunged 67 percent
to 407 million dollars from 1.23 billion in July.
</P>
<P>
In the year up to September, foreign investment were 4.63
billion dollars, a drop of 15.4 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The fall in investment was attributed to poor investor
sentiment following the financial turmoil that hit South Korea
late last year, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
"We expect foreign investment in Korea to begin a full-fledged
upward spiral in October since new legislation on foreign
investment was passed in September and because the government's
efforts to court foreign investment are expected to produce
results," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said investment through equity purchases of local
companies have increased sharply since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months, foreign investment through equity
purchases amounted to one billion dollars, accounting for 21.7
percent of total investments.
</P>
<P>
Of 92 projects worth more than 10 million dollars, 34 were in
the form of equity purchases, indicating that foreign investors
have been capitalizing on the lifting of restrictions on foreign
ownership of local companies.
</P>
<P>
Foreign direct investment in South Korea includes equity
purchases by foreigners of local companies on the over-the-counter
market and creation of independent or joint-venture companies,
said the ministry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
