<HEADLINE> Kunming Hosts Int'l Art Festival Organization Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Council of the
International Organization of Art Festival (CIOFA) opened its 29th
session today in Kunming, capital of southwest China's Yunnan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The CIOFA, with members from 74 countries and regions, was
established by United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural
Organization (UNESCO) in 1969.
</P>
<P>
The CIOFA has extended great effort to protect traditional
cultural and art forms around the world. China joined the
organization in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The 150-odd representatives from 58 countries and regions
attending the six-day event will discuss the role of women in
traditional culture.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts will present speeches concerning the role of
women in traditional culture and the cultural contributions of
women from ethnic nationalities.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,700 artists belonging to troupes from 10-odd countries
will perform during the simultaneous Sixth Asian Folk Arts
Festival which will open tomorrow.  
</P>
