<HEADLINE> China Grants DPRK 80,000 tons of Crude Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
decided to grant the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK)
80,000 tons of crude oil.
</P>
<P>
Sun Guangxiang, vice minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, and Chinese Ambassador to DPRK Wan Yongxiang today
informed the DPRK side of the decision in Beijing and Pyongyang,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK side expressed its heartfelt gratitude to China for
its grant, saying that such an aid will encourage the Korean
people to overcome the temporary difficulties.
</P>
<P>
DPRK understands the enormous losses caused by the
unprecedented devastating floods and holds China's grant is a
reflection of the traditional friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has already provided 100,000 tons of
cereals and 20,000 tons of chemical fertilizers to DPRK earlier
this year. 
