<HEADLINE> Malaysian New Navy Chief Assumes Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Royal Malaysian Navy's
deputy chief Rear Admiral Abu Bakar Abdul Jamal Thursday
officially assumed the duties of the Royal Malaysian Navy chief.
</P>
<P>
He took over from Rear Admiral Ahmad Ramli Mohd Noor in a
ceremony at the Ministry of Defense here, the Malaysian national
news Bernama said.
</P>
<P>
Ahmad Ramli is going on leave prior to retirement.
</P>
<P>
Abu Bakar, born on November 13, 1946, was commissioned as an
officer on September 1, 1968 after undergoing naval training at
the Britania Royal College in England.
</P>
<P>
He was appointed in 1982 Corvette Project Officer at the naval
headquarters, and in 1990 he was promoted to the post of commander
of Region One Naval Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
He was appointed as Royal Malaysian Navy assistant commander
(Human Resources) in January 1995 and later that year as navy
deputy chief. 
</P>
