<HEADLINE> German Exports Still on Rise Despite Asian, Russian Crises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Germany's exports grew by 4.4
percent year-on-year in August despite the economic crises in Asia
and Russia, the German Federal Statistics Office said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures released by the statistics office put
Germany's exports in August at 69.1 billion marks (42.3 billion
U.S. dollars), while imports grew by 2.3 percent from a year ago
to 60.5 billion marks (37 billion dollars), bringing a monthly
trade surplus of 8.6 billion marks (5.3 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
For the first eight months of this year as a whole, exports
surged 10.2 percent to a total of 628.1 billion marks (384.5
billion dollars) while imports grew by 7.7 percent to 538.9
billion marks (329.9 billion dollars), resulting in a total trade
surplus of 98.2 billion marks (60 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
