<HEADLINE> Outside Laborers to Macao Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Although the government had
pledged to cut laborers coming outside Macao this year, the actual
number of outside laborers turned out to rise over the same period
last year, Journal Va Kio reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Vitor Pessoa, secretary for economic coordination, was quoted
as saying Wednesday that the government is making efforts to
reduce the number of outside laborers, but the positive result
cannot be seen for the time being.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the increase was caused by the quota which
had been approved by the government earlier.
</P>
<P>
To ease unemployment in Macao, the government has cut or
restricted the number of outside laborers in the sectors of trade,
tourism and catering trade, said the secretary, adding that the
moves have to be carried out gradually.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the unemployment rate in
Macao hit 5.1 percent between June and August this year.
</P>
<P>
Asked when Macao's economy would turn better, Pessoa said that
the question was hard to answer, for the local economy is heavily
affected by depressive economic circumstances around Macao.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
