<HEADLINE> Asian Games Organizers Pledges to Abandon Emergency Venues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 15 (Xinhua)-- Organizers of Bangkok Asian
Games was determined on Thursday to give up emergency plans to
switch events after taking charge of the main sports complex for
the event.
</P>
<P>
The Muang Thong Thani complex was not completely finished for
Thursday's deadline for a handover to the organizers which has
passed quite a few sleepless nights by the delay-plague project.
</P>
<P>
The delays had so worried officials that they were forced to
make back-up plans to switch events to the northern city of
Chiang Mai and elsewhere before the regional competition start on
December 6.
</P>
<P>
"Nothing will be changed, the program is on schedule,"said
Sakchye Tapsuwan of the Sports Authority of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The facility will be used for the billiards, snooker, boxing,
gymnastics, rugby, tennis, volleyball and weightlifting.
</P>
<P>
It is also being used for tennis, boxing and gymnastics for
the three-day pre-games events which began Wednesday at Hua Mark
stadium in eastern Bangkok. 
