<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets South African Press People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Vice-President Hu Jintao, in a
meeting with a South African press delegation led by Jean-Jacques
Cornish, editor of The Star and SA Times this afternoon, discussed
China's reforms and economic development and said that China
values its ties with South Africa and that he appreciates the
contribution of South Africa's press to Sino-South African
relations.
</P>
<P>
Africa is a promising continent and the general situation there
is tending to ease up and is conducive to development, Hu said,
adding that Africa will rejuvenate itself in the next century as
long as African countries commit themselves to peace, stability
and progress, use regional advantages, and actively look for a
suitable road of economic revitalization.
</P>
<P>
China and South Africa are developing countries and China
places importance on South Africa's role in international and
African affairs and is ready to strengthen consultation and
cooperation with South Africa to safeguard the rights and
interests of the developing countries and world peace, he said.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to make a joint effort with South Africa to
explore new areas of bilateral relations based on the principle of
enhancing mutual understanding and trust, expanding cooperation
and achieving common progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
Cornish said that China impressed him and his colleagues deeply
and that they will devote themselves to promoting mutual
understanding and bilateral relations between China and South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
