<HEADLINE> Czech Team Scales Mount Pumori </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Three members of a Czech
team scaled the 7,161-meter Mount Pumori on Sunday from the
southeast side, the Nepali Ministry of Tourism and Civil Aviation
said in a press release Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Michal Ovsjannikov, Pavel Malek and Jaroslav Kovar, who are
all engineers, reached the summit at two o'clock in the
afternoon, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Team leader Jiri Svejda and three others failed, it added.
</P>
<P>
Mount Pumori is considered a technically difficult peak to
conquer.
</P>
<P>
Four members of a joint Australian-Canadian team ascended the
summit on October 7 and 9 from the rocky southwest face. 
