<HEADLINE> Overall Rice Production Good in Nepal: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- A poor harvest of rice is
expected in the Terai plain in southern Nepal due to flood and
pest, but the overall picture is good, an official at the Ministry
of Agriculture said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Kathmandu Post reported Thursday that after the receding of
flood caused by the recent monsoon, brown plant hoppers are now
making vast swaths of rice fields in Terai, Nepal's food bowl,
prematurely black.
</P>
<P>
Morang, Sunsari, Udaypur and Siraha in eastern Nepal and
Dhanusha in central Nepal are the districts hardest hit by the
pest, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The official RSS news agency reported Thursday that standing
paddy in about 600 hectares of land in Bara district of central
Nepal has been damaged by pests.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the Ministry of Agriculture Narayan Prasad Regmi
said Thursday that there was damage in some parts of the country
due to flood and other reasons but the overall picture of rice
production is good in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
