<HEADLINE> China Develops Effective Drug Rehabilitation Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
developed a traditional medicine, the "Fukang Tablet", which can
help rehabilitate drug users in six days.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came today at a conference sponsored by the
Traditional Chinese Medicine Administration, the International
Exchange Center of Traditional Chinese Medicine and the Gansu
Academy of National Science and Technology of China.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jihao, president of the Gansu Academy, said that the
tablet contains traditional Chinese and Tibetan medicine
ingredients produced with modern pharmaceutical techniques.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zuoning, a prominent Chinese psychiatrist, says that the
medicine can stop narcotic effects and relieve pain, strengthening
the body's resistance and eliminating pathogenic factors and
tranquilizing the mind.
</P>
<P>
It can get rid of toxins in the body of patients in three to
six days and help them withdraw completely from drug dependence,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Research on the medicine started ten years ago. In the past
three years, 68,000 patients have been rehabilitated with the help
of the medicine.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the United Nations show that there are 240
million drug addicts in the world, and about 100,000 people die
from drugs annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
