<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Development Zone And Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Fuzhou Development Zone in
the capital of east China's Fujian Province has reported success
in getting overseas investment in the first three quarters of this
year.
</P>
<P>
Agreements on 87 overseas-funded projects in the zone were
signed in the January-September period, with contracted overseas
investment of 280 million U.S. dollars, up 108 percent from the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the rapid increase to improved efforts
promoting fairs in Europe, the United States and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that nearly 700 overseas-funded projects
have been approved in the zone, with total investment of 3.1
billion U.S. dollars. 
