<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Burn Out-dated Fertilizer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Ministry of
Environmental Co-ordination Thursday issued a press communique
here saying the government will burn out-dated fertilizer in the
furnace of Mozambique Cement Company.
</P>
<P>
A survey by Mozambique's Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries
during 1994 and 1995 indicated that a total of 250 tons of
out-dated fertilizer were found in the country.
</P>
<P>
If they are not properly disposed, the fertilizer will pose
great damage to the environment. Experts suggest to gather all
the fertilizer together and burn them in the furnace of the
cement company which is located in Matola industrial town, about
10 km from the capital Maputo.
</P>
<P>
The Danish government has agreed to cooperate with Mozambique,
assisting in the disposal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
