<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Holds Talks With Swiss Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China's Defense Minister
General Chi Haotian, in a meeting with his Swiss counterpart Adolf
Ogi here today, said he believes that the visit will have an
enormous influence on friendship and cooperative relations between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers discussed the international and regional
situation and issues of common concern, and Chi expressed the hope
that military exchanges and cooperation between the two countries
can continue to increase on the basis of mutual respect and mutual
benefit.
</P>
