Relations Across the Taiwan Strait (ARATS) and Taiwan's Straits
Exchange Foundation (SEF) have decided to hold dialogues on various
topics, including political and economic issues, according to an
agreement between ARATS President Wang Daohan and SEF Chairman Koo
Chen-fu here today.
</P>
<P>
Tang Shubei, executive vice-president of ARATS, explained the
four-point agreement at a press briefing here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
ARATS and SEF have decided to hold dialogues and increase
exchanges between leaders at all levels.
</P>
<P>
ARATS and SEF are expected to increase assistance in individual
cases of livelihood and property security problems of compatriots
from the mainland and Taiwan, the agreement says.
</P>
<P>
Koo also used the meeting as an opportunity to invite Wang to
Taiwan. Wang thanked him for the invitation and hoped to visit
the island at a proper time.  
