<HEADLINE> Seminar on Hui History Opens In Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The First International
Seminar on the History and Culture of the Hui Ethnic Group opened
Tuesday in Yinchuan, capital of northwest China's "Muslim
province" -- Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 experts from 12 provinces, regions and
municipalities and from 11 countries and regions are attending the
conference.
</P>
<P>
The seminar will focus on such topics as the origins of the Hui
ethnic group, the differences and relations between Hui and other
Moslems and the contributions made by the Hui ethnic group to
China's history and culture.
</P>
<P>
Yu Zhengui, president of the Region's Academy of Social
Sciences, said this seminar is of significance to international
cultural exchanges and understanding among people of all
ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The Hui, one of China's national minorities, are of a lineage
including ancient Persians, Arabians, central Asians and Chinese
Han.
</P>
<P>
With 9 million members, the Hui minority group is the second
largest and most widespread ethnic group in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
