<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Meeting on Deaf Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The 10th World Federation of
the Deaf Regional Secretariat Asia and Pacific Representative
Meeting began here Thursday with focus on rehabilitation of the
deaf in the region.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the two-day meeting are 100 representatives
and observers from 13 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is organized by the Nepal National Federation of
the Deaf and Hard of Hearing.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that there are half a million deaf people in
Nepal alone.
</P>
<P>
Nepali Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala said in a message
to the meeting that the government is responsibly aware to uplift
the plight of the disabled people and help them lead an
undiscriminated life.
</P>
<P>
A workshop is scheduled for Saturday on U.N. standard rules on
the equalization of opportunities for persons with disabilities.
</P>
</TEXT>
