<HEADLINE> Compaq's Earning Falls By 78 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Compaq Computer Corp. of
the United States said Wednesday that its profits in the
July-September quarter fell by 78 percent to 115 million
U.S. dollars from 517 dollars a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
But according to the company's report, its sales jumped by 36
percent to 8.79 billion dollars from the 6.47 billion dollars the
company reported last year.
</P>
<P>
One major reason behind the fall of earnings and rise of sales,
said market analysts, is Compaq's integration recently acquired by
Digital Equipment Corp.
</P>
<P>
Compaq, the world largest personal computer manufacturer, said
it had closed six overseas plants and eliminated 5,000 jobs,
including 1,000 at its Houston headquarters as part of a
cost-cutting drive following the Digital acquisition.
</P>
<P>
"The third quarter was the first full quarter of operating the
combined companies of Compaq and Digital," Eckhard Pfeiffer,
Compaq's president and chief executive, said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
However, Pfeiffer said his company will achieve continued
strong growth in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
