<HEADLINE> Mubarak Briefed on Ethiopia-Eritrea Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
Thursday received a message from Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles
Zenawi on the developing crisis on the Ethiopian-Eritrean border.
</P>
<P>
The message was delivered by Ethiopian Foreign Minister Seyoum
Mesfin to Mubarak during their meeting which focused on the
Ethiopian-Eritrean crisis.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Mesfin told reporters that the message dealt
with the present situation between Ethiopia and Eritrea,
Egyptian-Ethiopian relations and problems facing the Horn of
Africa in general.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian top diplomat, who arrived here Thursday,
expressed regret over the present situation, noting that chances
for a peaceful settlement are still "unclear."
</P>
<P>
But he expressed hope for the mediation efforts by the
Organization of African Unity to succeed in sending proposals to
all parties next month.
</P>
<P>
Mesfin said the main objective of his visit was to discuss ways
to enhance relations between Egypt and Ethiopia and that his
meeting with the Egyptian president was a good opportunity to
exchange views on a number of major African issues of mutual
interest.
</P>
<P>
Mesfin's visit as a number of African presidents are making a
proposal for solving the Ethiopian-Eritrean border dispute.
</P>
<P>
According to African sources, the new proposal has been frowned
upon by Eritrea because it entails Asmara's pullout from Ethiopian
territory it occupied in the wake of armed clashes between the two
countries in May.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the new proposal also provides for sending an
African peacekeeping force to run the area pending negotiations
between Asmara and Addis Ababa on disputed border areas. 
</P>
