edible oil and corn to Russia in the hope of regaining the
important market, said Agriculture and Food Minister Dinu
Gavrilescu.
</P>
<P>
An economic mission is expected to go to Russia for talks on
the export, Gavrilescu was quoted by the country's Nine O'clock
daily as saying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said that Romania has stockpiled for export quantities of
meat amounting to "scores of thousand tons," 100,000 tons of
export-bound edible oil and 500,000 tons of additional
corn. Besides, massive quantities of chicken and wine are also
available for export.
</P>
<P>
"The Russian market is a purely financial question and they
will probably resort to a barter for natural gas and crude oil,"
Gavrilescu said.
</P>
<P>
The situation of agriculture in Russia is reportedly rather
critical. Corn production will likely drop to 50-60 million tons
this year compared with 88.5 million tons in 1997 and 106.8
million tons in 1992. 
