<HEADLINE> Philippines Sets Up Remittance Center for Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine National Bank
(PNB) announced here Thursday that it has set up a remittance call
center to serve the needs of overseas Filipino workers and their
beneficiaries.
</P>
<P>
The PNB said in a statement that the remittance call center
will provide easy access and quick response to inquiries on the
status of incoming remittances.
</P>
<P>
Instead of going to PNB branches to check on the availability
of remittances, all the beneficiaries need to do now is to simply
dial the number of a hotline connected to the PNB's overseas
remittance division, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the beneficiaries will be quickly apprised by the
bank's customer service officers on the status of their expected
remittances.
</P>
<P>
The PNB advised clients not to worry about busy signal because
the hotline has a total of 10 dedicated lines. In case all these
lines are engaged, the incoming call is automatically routed to
the bank's telephone operators.
</P>
<P>
As of June this year, the PNB has processed over a million
overseas remittances valued at 1.27 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines has about six million overseas workers in more
than 100 countries and regions. These workers are expected to
remit six billion U.S. dollars back to the country this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
