Asia-Pacific Parliamentarians Conference on Environment and
Development opened today in Guilin, a city famous for its scenery
in south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, addressed the meeting and called on
all countries to protect the environment and promote sustainable
development.
</P>
<P>
China has adopted environmental protection as a basic state
policy, taking a series of steps to protect the environment and
ecological surroundings, he said, adding that with population and
economic growth, China is facing serious challenges in protecting
its environment and resources.
</P>
<P>
China, however, is confident of finding solutions to these
problem through unremitting efforts and in cooperation with other
countries, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Pete Hodgson, acting chairman of the Executive Council of the
General Assembly of the Asia-Pacific Parliamentarians Conference
on Environment and Development, said at the opening ceremony that
environmental protection must go ahead of development, and the
close relationship between environmental protection and
development will be further discussed at the conference.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from 27 Asia-Pacific countries and
international organizations are attending the general assembly
whose theme is "protection of environment and resources, and
sustainable development of tourism." 
