<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee met with leaders of non-Communist parties,
the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, and persons
without party affiliation on September 11 to discuss agriculture
and rural work issues.
</P>
<P>
The CPC wanted to hear their opinions on the Central
Committee's decision on agriculture and rural work that was
to be discussed at the Third Plenary Session of the 15th
Central Committee of the CPC in Beijing on October 12 and 14.
</P>
