<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10,000 People Perform Taiji at Tian'anmen Suqare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000 people
performed Chinese traditional art of Taiji shadow boxing in
Tian'anmen Square, Beijing, on Thursday in memory of Deng
Xiaoping's inscription "great Taiji".
</P>
<P>
Ages of participants range from 16-82, although most were aged
50 or over. The majority live in Beijing but some had came from
as far away as Chinese Taipei, Macao and Hebei province.
</P>
<P>
Also taking part were foreign visitors from all over the
world, including Japan, America and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first of its kind to be held in China. I feel
proud of the spectacle!" said Yan Jianchang, general-secretary of
Chinese Wushu Association (CWA)
</P>
<P>
The display was held not only to mark the 20th anniversary of
Deng Xiaoping's famous remark about the healthy quality of Taiji
shadow boxing to Japanese friends, but also the 40th anniversary
of the establishment of CWA.
</P>
<P>
Taiji shadow boxing a branch of Wushu, which was regarded as
the Chinese traditional culture treasure, is one of the most popu
lar sport in people's life. In recent years. the traditional art
opens its door and spreads all over the world.
</P>
<P>
The International Wushu Association (IWA) has attracted
members from 77 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
"IWA and CWA will submit its application to the International
Olympic Committee for identification at the end of this year,"
Yan revealed.
</P>
<P>
"But that is not the purpose of the 10,000 people performance
today. Our aim is to promote the Chinese traditional art to the
world, and contribute the fitness to the all human beings."
</P>
<P>
The 10,000 white-clad performers were picked from a total of
more than 80 million Taiji fans under the control of CWA.
</P>
<P>
"I played Taiji for more than 20 years. I enjoyed the
combination of philosophical and physical exercise every
morning." said a 59-year-old women, who retired from China Social
Science Academy,
</P>
<P>
The 3-million RMB yuan display, which the organizers are
hoping to be an annual event, also attracted many foreigners to
come.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese Wushu and Taiji shadow boxing become popular in our
country," said an Australian tourist who saw the spectacle from
the very begining," The slow-motion is good for aged people, even
our foreigners." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
