<HEADLINE> Japanese Prime Minister Welcomes Wang-Koo Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Keizo
Obuchi Thursday welcomed talks held Wednesday in Shanghai between
Wang Daohan, president of the Association for Relations Across the
Taiwan Straits, and Koo Chen-fu, chairman of the Taiwan-based
Straits Exchange Foundation.
</P>
<P>
"I welcome the development," Obuchi told reporters at his
official residence.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi said he personally knows Wang and Koo, adding that they
are both "trustworthy, experienced people."
</P>
<P>
"I hope the two are able to hold thorough discussions," Obuchi
said.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time that leaders of the authorized
non-governmental organizations on both sides of the Taiwan Straits
have met on the mainland since their establishment in the early
1990s.
</P>
<P>
The first Wang-Koo meeting was held in 1993 in Singapore.
</P>
