<HEADLINE> Chinese Government's View On Kosovo Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Tang Guoqiang, when asked here today to comment on the
recent agreement on Kosovo between Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic and U.S. special envoy Richard Holbrooke, said that
China hopes that the parties involved can solve the problem with
constructive stance.
</P>
<P>
China welcomes the positive developments concerning Kosovo and
has always believed that it should be settled peacefully, he said,
and that China has made an effort to help find a peaceful solution
of the issue.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, in recent messages to UN
Secretary General Kofi Annan and foreign ministers in the United
States, Russia, Britain and France, explained China's stand on the
Kosovo issue, Tang said, and asked the parties concerned to adopt
effective measures for a political solution to the crisis and to
avoid the use of force. 
</P>
