<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Technical Assistance to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
said Thursday that it will provide a technical assistance grant of
1.2 million U.S. dollars for a regional road study to improve road
transport facilities in southwestern China.
</P>
<P>
The study will assess the economic and social impact of
selected road sector investments, the Manila-based bank said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the study will result in a set of road investment
packages, including expressway sections, provincial, county and
village road, capacity-building actions and policy issues for the
development of the region.
</P>
<P>
The provinces of Guizhou, Sichuan and Yunnan, the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region and the Municipality of Chongqing will
benefit from the program, the ADB said. 
