<HEADLINE> China Pays Close Attention Environmental Protection: Li Peng (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to attach
vital importance to changing the mode of economic growth and take
the path of sustainable development in future economic
development, Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress(NPC) stressed today.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the
remarks at the 6th General Assembly of the Asia-Pacific
Parliamentarians' Conference on Environment and Development, which
opened today in Guilin, a famous scenic city in south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Li first extended a cordial welcome to the parliamentary
delegations of all countries and to all guests attending the
conference.
</P>
<P>
"The NPC of the People's Repubic of China(PRC) has made careful
preparations for the assembly with the full support and
participation of the relevant departments of the Chinese
government and local governments," Li said, adding that he was
convinced that the successful convocation of the General Assembly
will play a positive role in promoting economic prosperity,
environmental protection and the sound development of tourism in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government attaches great importance to the issues
of environment and development, he stressed, adding that it
decided to attach vital importance to changing the mode of
economic growth and take the path of sustainable development in
future economic development.
</P>
<P>
Li listed following items as important and arduous tasks which
China is confronted with: Implementing the strategy of correctly
handling the relationship between economic development,
population, resources and the environment, rationally developing
and making comprehensive use of resources and protecting and
improving the ecological environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
