<HEADLINE> Improving Telecommunications In Countryside Of Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 15 (Xinhua) --Telecommunications have
improved a lot in Liaoning Province, where there were a million
rural telephone customers by September.
</P>
<P>
Ninety percent of the province's administrative villages can
be reached by phone, and 900,000 rural households have phone
lines. This is a dramatic change from before 1988, when phone
service was scarce.
</P>
<P>
In the past several years, the province has put a large amount
of money to build 20,000 km of fiber-optic cables for townships. The
computer-controlled telephone switchboards in rural areas can
handle 1.4 million phone calls simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
The modern telecommunications network provides local farmers
with ways to learn about practical farming techniques and market
information via e-mail or the Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
