<HEADLINE> Foreign-funded Enterprises Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The 11th national trade fair
of export commodities made by foreign-funded enterprises opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
On display are industrial, machinery, chemical and straw and
rattan products provided by 500 foreign-funded firms across China.
</P>
<P>
The fair was organized by the China Association for
Foreign-funded Enterprises, which has recruited 100,000 members
since it was founded in November 1987.
</P>
<P>
The previous fair attracted more than 40,000 traders
from 100 countries and regions and produced contracts with a
total value of 1.6 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The import and export volume of foreign-funded enterprises has
maintained a steady grow since 1979 with the figure climbing to
152 billion U.S. dollars in 1997, up 11.3 percent over the
previous year. These enterprises account for 46.9 percent of
China's total import and export value.  
</P>
</TEXT>
