<DOCNO> XIE19981015.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Draw Electricity from Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania will get 200
megawatts of power supplies from the neighboring Zambia under a
153 million U.S. Dollars agreement.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, signed between the state-owned Tanzania
Electric Supply Company (TANESCO) and its counterpart Zambia
Electricity Supply Corporation (ZESCO), offers to build a
700-kilometer 330-kv transmission line in three years.
</P>
<P>
According to Tanzanian newspapers Thursday, the line will
extend from Zambia's Serenje to Tanzania's Mbeya Region in the
southwest.
</P>
<P>
By the time the project is completed, Tanzania, which is
plagued by shortage of electricity, will draw less expensive
power from Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The project, whose feasibility study took four years, will
further enable TANESCO to fully participate in the Southern
African Power Pool which aims to create a common market for
electricity in the 14-nation Southern Africa Development
Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
The accord, which was sealed in Lusaka Tuesday, said an
environmental impact assessment study of the project has been
carried out to identify possible adverse effects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
