<HEADLINE> Highest Science Body Supports Backward Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China's highest scientific
research institute announced today that it will support the
underdeveloped Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region with the most
advanced high technologies.
</P>
<P>
"While organizing our elite experts to focus on the most
sophisticated frontiers of modern science, the academy will
mobilize the major force to help develop the national and regional
economy," said Lu Yongxiang, president of the Chinese Academy of
Sciences (CAS).
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia's economy consists mainly of farming, animal
husbandry and mining.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1950s, the CAS has established observatories for
surveying the natural resources and ecological environment of the
region.
</P>
<P>
"We should further develop our cooperation with the region in
the field of scientific upgrading," Lu said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to its long-term research on the agriculture, ecology
and the environment of the region, the CAS will provide
decision-makers with its development projects.
</P>
<P>
The technology will include support for harnessing the desert
and improving farming and mineral exploitation.
</P>
<P>
China's highest authorities recently decided to invigorate
agriculture through science and technology and earnestly protect
natural resources and the environment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
