<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Minister of Culture,
Youth and Sports Mateus Kathupa has urged the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) countries to launch organized
campaign against piracy.
</P>
<P>
Kathupa made the call here Wednesday at a press conference. He
said Mozambique suffered serious loss due to piracy in
audio-visual products and the information sector.
</P>
<P>
