said 15 employees of a hydro-thermal power firm in a mountainous
town in Benguet province, the northern Philippines, were declared
missing following a landslide Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Confirmation of the information was difficult because the
communication lines to the power firm were bogged down, the office
said.
</P>
<P>
Supertyphoon Zeb with sustained center winds of 245 kilometers
per hour lashed the northern Philippines Wednesday, causing
serious damage to the country. 
