<HEADLINE> Symposium on Bankruptcy Legal Affairs Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- An international symposium on
business bankruptcy, reorganization and acquisition out of
insolvency is being held in Beijing from October 14 to 16.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 100 Chinese and foreign lawyers, business executives,
bankers and court officials are attending the symposium, which is
jointly sponsored by the All-China Lawyers Association and the
U.S. firm of Vinson &AMP; Elkins L.L.P.
</P>
<P>
The symposium highlights international legal affairs practices
in cases of business bankruptcy, reorganization and acquisition
out of insolvency and their specific applications in China.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is intended to inform lawyers and others
on the progress of legislation in China's dealing with these
issues.
</P>
<P>
During the symposium, D. Bobbitt Noel, Jr. and Kevin P. Lewis
and five other partners from Vinson &AMP; Elkins L.L.P. delivered
reports on recognizing companies and firms with reorganization
potential, fundamentals of business reorganization, reorganization
planning of assets and debts, and liquidation and acquisition.
</P>
<P>
Qin Xiao, president of the China International Trust and
Investment Corporation, spoke on the implementation of strategic
reorganization of state-owned businesses.
</P>
<P>
"This is an important step in the restructuring of China's
microeconomy, showing China's attitudes towards new restructuring
tides in the world market and tendencies of globalization," Qin
said.
</P>
<P>
Participants believe that lawyers will play an active role in
business bankruptcy, reorganization and acquisition out of
insolvency, since there are many legal issues involved in the
process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
