<HEADLINE> China Expects Good Grain Harvest This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Despite heavy summer flooding,
China is expected to harvest 492.5 billion kg of grain this year,
roughly the same as last year's output, the Ministry of
Agriculture said today.
</P>
<P>
The harvest of cotton is predicted at 1.6 million kg this year,
though the acreage sown to the crop had been reduced, said the
ministry.
</P>
<P>
The annual output of autumn oil-bearing crops is expected to
surpass that of last year, though oil-bearing crops harvested this
summer was greatly reduced.
</P>
<P>
Sugar-bearing crops, vegetables, fruits, tea and silkworm
cocoons also are expected to have good harvests.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributes the anticipated good harvest to the
application of modern agricultural techniques and a higher rate of
mechanization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
