<P>
The police in the city of Baoshan recently received a report
from local residents that a restaurant on Baoxiu West Road was
serving giant lizards that enjoy first-class government protection.
</P>
<P>
As part of their investigation, police officers called the
restaurant and pretended to order a banquet. During the bargaining
they were told that the restaurant had a special dish--chicken and
lizard soup.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon, plainclothes policemen came to the restaurant
and asked to see if the giant lizard was fresh or not. The owner
of the restaurant, Hao Huijie, then proceeded to take two
prepeared giant lizards out of the ice box.
</P>
<P>
Policemen had caught the restaurant redhanded, and confiscated
the giant lizards on the spot. After careful examination,
specialist confirmed they were indeed the wild giant lizards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
