<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats Ecuador 5-1 in Soccer Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Elber scored three times
to boost Brazil to rout Ecuador in a friendly soccer match here
tonight.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time for the new Brazilian national team to
play since losing 3-0 to France in the World Cup final three
months ago.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has beaten Ecuador, a team failed to qualify for the
World Cup finals this summer, 71-14 in 19 games.
</P>
<P>
Besides Elber's three goals, Marcelinho Carioca scored in the
22nd minute and Cafu netted in the 70th minute.
</P>
<P>
Elber, who replaced injuried Ronaldo tonight, is one of the
top scorers in the German league for Bayern Munich. He found the
net in the 35th, 71st and 78th minutes. The 26-year-old forward
has five goals in five career international appearances.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador, 2-0 behind after the first half, shot in its sole
goal through Ulises De La Cruz in the 67th minute. 
