<DOCNO> XIE19981015.0286 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM Calls for Int'l Cooperation to Tackle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina has called for international cooperation and initiative to
tackle natural disaster, English newspapers here reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
She made the call Wednesday while addressing the inaugural
function on International Decade for Natural Disaster Reduction
Day '98 in Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Different countries might be the victims of the same disaster
simultaneously as this year's devastating floods in China, Nepal,
India and South Korea at the same time, she observed.
</P>
<P>
Her government is thinking of preparing and implementing
development programs to cope with natural disasters, the prime
minister said. "For this, we are going to prepare far-reaching
programs."
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is a natural disaster-prone country, and quite often
heavy loss of life and properties are caused by natural disasters
like cyclone, tidal surge, flood, river erosion, drought and
earthquake, Hasina told the function.
</P>
<P>
"It is humanly impossible to prevent natural disasters
totally," she said, adding that it is necessary to make the
structural reform and development on the one hand and wide
publicity about disaster on the other.
</P>
<P>
With the coordination of these two, it is possible to reduce to
a great extent the loss and damages caused by disaster, Hasina
stressed. Side by side with the government initiatives,
cooperation and all-out efforts of the mass media is important in
this regard, she stated.
</P>
<P>
"We've ensured all-out and effective use of our mass media in
reducing the havoc caused by natural disasters," the prime
minister said.
</P>
<P>
About the far-reaching programs, she stressed the need for
dredging of rivers, saying "dredging of our big rivers will be
made to reduce the probabilities of flood as well as to increase
their navigability".
</P>
<P>
The government buildings like schools, colleges and hospitals
would be built in such way that they could be used as flood and
cyclone shelters in flood-and cyclone-prone areas of the country,
Hasina said, adding that the height of highways and roads would
also be raised from the present level.
</P>
<P>
She said that the government had decided to construct an
embankment to keep the capital city of Dhaka free from flooding.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the government was planning to take initiative to
plant such variety of paddy and crops that could be able to grow
up higher with the rise of flood water, the prime minister added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
