<HEADLINE> Preparations Accelerate for '99 World Garden-Art Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The construction of exhibition
halls and the preparation of exhibits for the '99 Kunming World
Garden-Art Fair will be completed by the end of next March,
according to the China National Tourism Administration (CNTA).
</P>
<P>
The fair will be the only large-scale international event held
by the Chinese government before the end of this century. From May
1 to October 31, 1999, more than eight million people from 60
nations, 20 international organizations and all Chinese
provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions, as well as
thousands of journalists are expected to visit the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
China will spend more than one billion yuan (120.48 million
U.S. dollars) building exhibition halls and another 400 million
yuan (48.19 million U.S. dollars) beautifying the site with
greenery, trees and flowers, the CNTA said.
</P>
<P>
More than half the work for this project already has been
completed. Construction of the international hall, a major part
for the project, has been completed, according to a local source.
</P>
<P>
The Kunming city government is trying to improve infrastructure
by raising the annual handling capacity of the Kunming Airport to
seven million people from the existing two million, and increasing
the daily reception capacity of local hotels from 20,000 people to
50,000. All personnel who will be working at the fair have
received special training.
</P>
<P>
The CNTA plans to attract more than one million overseas
tourists and more than nine million domestic visitors to the fair,
which will be an important part of the '99 China Ecological
Tourism Year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
