<HEADLINE> Cuba Welcomes U.N. Rejection of U.S. Blockade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States isolation in
pursuing its policy to Cuba has grown as 157 members of the
U.N. General Assembly voted for a resolution calling for
Washington to repeal its embargo, Cuba said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Xinhua, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Alejandro Gonzalez noted that only two countries, the
United States and Israel, voted in favor of the sanctions imposed
by the United States in 1959 and 12 others abstained.
</P>
<P>
Gonzalez said that the U.S. policy violates human rights and
the basic rule of respecting other independent states.
</P>
<P>
Many countries have been aware of the adverse impact of the
policy. The nearly four-decade long U.S. blockade has brought
damages not only to Cuba, but to the international stability as
well, Gonzalez said. 
</P>
