<HEADLINE> Asia-Europe Cable System Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 15 (Xinhua) -- The Asia-Europe optical fiber
cable system began operation Wednesday, becoming an important
channel of the global telecommunications network.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony was held simultaneously in 11 Asian and European
countries Wednesday afternoon to launch the shortest and most
effective telecommunication link between Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The 27,000 kilometer-long system, starting in Shanghai and
going through 20 countries in central Asia and Europe, mainly
follows the ancient silk road, the historic trade route between
Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
It is currently the world's longest cable system, which covers
some 6,000 kilometers within China before going out to the rest of
the world in the western part of the country into Kazakhstan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
