<HEADLINE> China Sees Rapid Growth of Revenues in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial and
commercial tax income in September reached 71.63 billion yuan, an
increase of 12.4 billion yuan, or 20.9 percent, on a yearly basis,
according to the latest statistics released by the State
Administration of Taxation (SAT).
</P>
<P>
The growth rate was the highest in the past nine months.
</P>
<P>
Of the revenues in September, 42.4 billion yuan went to the
central government, up 19.2 percent from the same month last year,
while 29.2 billion yuan went to local governments, up 23.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Delayed taxes by enterprises were reduced further, with an
outstanding amount of 39.8 billion yuan at the end of the month,
down 13.8 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
In total, the country's industrial and commercial tax income
finished 586.6 billion yuan in the first nine months, up 9.3
percent from the same period last year or an increase of 50
billion yuan, accomplishing 70.3 percent of the whole year
target.  
</P>
</TEXT>
