<HEADLINE> Hungary Approves NATO Request to Use Air Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian National
Assembly Wednesday approved the government's proposal to allow the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization's (NATO) aircraft to fly over
its territory in the event of military action against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was passed by most parliament members from six
parties during a special meeting.
</P>
<P>
All members of the Federation of Young Democrats-Hungarian
Civic Party (Fidesz), the Independent Smallholders Party (FKGP),
the Alliance of Free Democrats (SZDSZ) and most of the Hungarian
Democratic Forum (MDF) and the Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP)
voted for the proposal.
</P>
<P>
But all MPs from the Hungarian Justice and Life Party (MIEP),
and several MPs from the MDF and the MSZP voted against the
proposal.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that once NATO launches its threatened air
attacks on Yugoslavia over the Kosovo crisis, alliance's aircraft
will use Hungarian air space during a second round of air strikes,
which could occur about a week after the first round of strikes.
</P>
