<HEADLINE> Green City Attracts Bird Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Trees have been planted along
the banks of the Lijiang River in the tourist city of Guilin in
southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, attracting
thousands of migratory birds.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the city has spent 60 million yuan on an
afforestation project aimed to plant trees on a 40,000-hectare
space along the river banks. Half of the job has been done so far.
</P>
<P>
The city has also hired farmers as environmental protection
staff and set up two afforestation supervision centers and 5,656
methane-generating pits.
</P>
