<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Loans to Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) agreed on Wednesday to provide Argentina
with 375 million U.S. dollars to improve the country's gas-supply
service.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to finance a 5-year capital investment
plan of the Gas Carrier of the South company, one of the two
natural gas companies operating in Argentina, said a communique of
the bank.
</P>
<P>
The money will help the company enhance the efficiency, safety
and reliability of its services and to extend its existing
gas-pipe network.
</P>
<P>
The credit consists of a loan of 75 million dollars as ordinary
capital from the bank and 300 million dollars from institutional
investment funds under the subscription of participation
agreements with the bank. 
</P>
