<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Set to Achieve Economic Objectives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is well on track for
achieving its economic objectives this year.
</P>
<P>
"The economic situation in the first three quarters means we
can achieve the 9-percent growth rate set for this year," Pan Fan,
vice-director of Beijing Statistics Bureau, was quoted as saying
by today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Pan said that in the January-September period, Beijing's gross
domestic product totalled 139.3 billion yuan (16.8 billion US
dollars), up 9.6 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
With industrial growth as the locomotive, every aspect from
production to consumption is looking good, Pan said.
</P>
<P>
In September, Beijing's industrial added value reached a record
high for this year, amounting to 5.06 billion yuan (610 million US
dollars), 21.8 percent up on September last year and 2 percent up
on last August.
</P>
<P>
In January and September this year, monthly retail turnover in
Beijing exceeded 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) for the
first time.
</P>
<P>
Beijing invested 57.54 billion yuan (6.9 billion US dollars) in
real estate in the year to September. Foreign trade amounted to
45.61 billion yuan (5.5 billion US dollars), with exports rising
24.3 percent and imports 13.7 percent over 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
