<HEADLINE> World Bank Provides Line of Credit For Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chile has received a line of
credit from the World Bank to finance projects that will encourage
science and technological development.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Eduardo Aninat said on Wednesday that the
first loan of 145 million U.S. dollars will assist in promoting higher
education in the country, and the second loan of 5 million dollars
will be used to develop scientific research centers.
</P>
<P>
With the credit, Aninat said his government will attempt to
improve the country's science and technology development, which
has fallen far behind the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
"This is an issue of concern since we know these areas are
becoming more and more critical for realizing the full potential
of our economy," he said. 
