<HEADLINE> Brazil, Paraguay to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazil and Paraguay reaffirmed
Wednesday their aim to strengthen cooperation among the Southern
Common Market (Mercosur) member countries.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Foreign Minister Luiz Felipe Lampreia and his
Paraguayan counterpart Dido Florentin Bogado said Wednesday that
they will continue to extend free trade agreements to other South
American countries.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur is made up of Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay,
with Bolivia and Chile as associates.
</P>
<P>
Bogado his country and Brazil would continue to work closely
together to combat drug trafficking, terrorism and smuggling.
</P>
<P>
He said the Paraguayan government had made the regularization
of Brazilian immigrants a top priority with the issuing of
residence cards to properly registered citizens to be completed
next year.  
