<HEADLINE> Myanmar Strives to Develop Computer Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar computer associations
are trying to get support from regional and international
counterparts to enhance the development of the country's computer
technology, especially the systematic development of information
technology.
</P>
<P>
The Mastech Co Ltd of Myanmar and the XYBASE Technologies of
Malaysia jointly held an information technology forum here Tuesday
as a part of the cooperation between the computer associations of
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In June, Myanmar held the First Symposium on Information
Technology Initiative to promote the development and advancement
of computer technology in the country.
</P>
<P>
With a view to systematic development of information technology
in Myanmar, the government promulgated the Computer Technology
Development Law in September 1996, and later founded the Computer
Technology Development Council.
</P>
<P>
In this year, three associations of the Myanmar computer
technicians, entrepreneurs and enthusiasts were also respectively
formed in May and July.
</P>
<P>
To assist in developing the information technology needed for
the country, the government is also making arrangement to
establish the Myanmar Computer Federation based on these three
associations.
</P>
<P>
In cooperation with Japanese computer organizations, the
Myanmar Computer Federation is scheduled to hold the Myanmar-Japan
Bilateral Conference on Information Technology Cooperation on
November 10 this year.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar Computer Federation is expected to be accepted as
an organization representing Myanmar at the annual conference of
the Asian Oceanian Computing Industry Organization (ASOCIO) to be
held on November 25 to 26 in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The country started computerized teaching at universities and
institutes in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar successfully launched the first interactive CD in May
this year on "Myanmar Another Incarnation," which covers various
aspects of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
