<HEADLINE> European Experts to Discuss Euro's Impact on Latin America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The impact of Europe's
single currency -- the euro -- on Latin America will be discussed
at an international conference here on Thursday, press reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials of the European Commission (EC) and the
European Investment Bank (EIB) will join leading representatives
of Uruguay's industry, finance and academic circles at the
conference.
</P>
<P>
Head of the EC delegation Joel Fessaguet told the press on
Wednesday that the euro, which goes into formal circulation on
January 1, 1999, constitutes an authentic "big bang" with
worldwide repercussions.
</P>
<P>
Director of the EC's North-South Relations Office Pierre
Defraigne is scheduled to make a keynote speech briefing the
conference on the process to construct the European Economic and
Monetary Union and the euro "as a response to the globalization
challenge."
</P>
<P>
Senior EC advisor Christian Ghymers will present macroeconomic
policies of the euro regime and offer practical information on how
to handle transactions in euros.
</P>
<P>
EIB representative Eric Peree will speak on relations between
the euro and the future capital market.
</P>
<P>
The European experts on Wednesday gave a series of similar
conferences in Argentina. After the conference in Uruguay, they
will travel to Chile on Friday for the same purpose. 
</P>
</TEXT>
