<DOCNO> XIE19981015.0329 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile's Manufacturing Exports Grow 5.3 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Chile's manufacturing exports
grew 5.3 percent in the first seven months of 1998, compared to
the same period in 1997, show figures released recently by the
Manufacture Exporters Association.
</P>
<P>
Reports of the association said manufacturing exports, amounting
to 1.67 billion U.S. dollars in the seven months, grew while the
country's total exports fell 12.7 percent during the period.
</P>
<P>
The transport sector led the growth, rising 63.5 percent,
followed by wine exports with a 33.5 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
But sea products conserves and agroindustry exports dropped
by 17.2 percent and 14.8 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The biggest sales were directed to Venezuela, Japan and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The sharpest fall was recorded in exports to Brazil, down by
10.1 percent. The downturn has produced strong impact to
agroindustrial and copper manufacturing sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
