<HEADLINE> Brazil's Coffee Exports Grow 66% in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazil exported
2.1 million sacks (60 kilograms each) of coffee last September,
registering a 66 percent growth compared with the same month
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released by the Brazilian Coffee Exporters
Association (ABECAFE) on Wednesday, during the first nine months
of the year, Brazil, the world's major coffee producer and
exporter, exported more than 11.312 million coffee-sacks.
</P>
<P>
Due to low prices abroad, Brazil's earnings from coffee sales
in the first nine months fell 18 percent from the same period last
year, according to ABECAFE.
</P>
<P>
The association added that Brazil's coffee exports in 1997
earned nearly 2.7 billion U.S. dollars. 
