<HEADLINE> Davenport Wins Opening Match at Euro Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 14 (Xinhua) -- American Lindsay Davenport won
her opening match as the world's top-ranked woman on Wednesday,
beating French qualifier Julie Halard-Decugis in two straight
sets at the European Tennis Championships in Zurich.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old American needed 58 minutes to win from
Halard-Decugis 6-4, 6-2 for a place in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Third-seed Conchita Martinez became the first seeded player to
get knocked out of the tournament, losing 6-2, 7-6 (7-0) to
Romania's Irina Spirlea.
</P>
<P>
In earlier second round play, seventh-seed Mary Pierce of
France edged South African Joanette Kruger 7-6 (8-6), 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seed Amanda Coetzer of South Africa easily entered the
quarter-finals with a 6-3, 6-1 victory over Romania's Ruxandra
Dragomir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
