<HEADLINE> Industrial Production Up in Central China's Henan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 15 (Xinhua) -- Industrial enterprises in
central China's Henan Province reported a 5.9-percent annual
increase in added value which totaled 65.8 billion yuan in the
first nine months of the year.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial statistics bureau, the province
witnessed the fastest growth in industrial production in
September, when industrial enterprises generated 8.08 billion yuan
in added value, 814 million yuan more than the previous month and
up 8.9 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
Of the 65.8 billion yuan worth of added value, 37.1 billion
yuan was accomplished by state-owned and state-controlled
industrial enterprises, up by 2.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the past nine months, added value generated by
collectively-owned industries rose by 11.8 percent, and that done
by large and medium-sized enterprises in the province grew 2.1
percent to 33.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the state's increased investment in improving
infrastructure and spurring domestic demand, the province saw a
faster growth in heavy industrial production and production of
some raw materials. Heavy industrial enterprises in the province
completed 41.1 billion yuan of added value from January to
September, up by 8.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the marketing of locally produced goods also
experienced significant improvement. Henan sold 198.1 billion yuan
worth of manufactured goods in the first nine months this year, up
4.7 percent, and achieved a marketing-production ratio of 95.62
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
