<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Credits for Niger, Armenia Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Wednesday
announced the approval of two interest-free credits totaling 72
million U.S. dollars to finance projects in Niger and Armenia.
</P>
<P>
First credit of 64 million dollars is earmarked for Niger's
public financial reform project.
</P>
<P>
This project will help sustain the government's economic reform
program by restoring credibility of public finance.
</P>
<P>
Second credit of 8 million dollars will be provided to back
land registration project in Armenia.
</P>
<P>
The project will create a parcel-based registration system for
land and other property, providing a chronological record of
property owners and their rights and obligations.
</P>
<P>
The credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending wing for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
