<HEADLINE> Dow up 30 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 14 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks rebounded on
Wednesday amid encouraging reports of some blue-chip companies on
their third quarter performance.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average zigzagged from an early 60
point fall to a 99 point surge, and closed 30.64 points higher at
7968.78, still below the 8000 level but above this year's starting
point of 7908.25, according to preliminary figures.
</P>
<P>
Broader market indicators also posted gains with the
technology-heavy Nastaq composite index up 31.52 to 1540.97, and
the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 up 10.73 to 1005.53.
</P>
<P>
Among the Dow's 30 component companies, chip maker Intel and
computer maker Compaq gained as their third quarter earnings were
up or within analysts' expectations.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange, advancing issues led decliners
3-2 with trading volume totaling 782 million shares, against 725
million on the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index was up 4.48 to 496.98 and the American
Stock Exchange composite index was up 5.15 to 583.01.
</P>
<P>
Bourses in Asia and Europe were mixed with Tokyo's NiKKei stock
average down 1.3 percent, Frankfurt's DAX index up 1.0 percent,
London's FT-SE 100 up 1.0 percent and Paris's CAC-40 up 2.5
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
