<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing to Back Natural Gas Pipeline in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) Wednesday announced the approval of up to
375 million U.S. dollars in financing for the expansion of
Argentine natural gas pipeline company.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be used to support the five-year capital
investment plan of Transportadora de Gas del Sur S.A., one of the
country's two private sector natural gas transportation companies.
</P>
<P>
The resources will contribute to the company's expansion,
technological improvement, efficiency, safety and reliability.
Among the activities that will be financed are the expansion and
enhancement of existing pipelines.
</P>
<P>
The IDB package consists of a loan from ordinary capital of up
to 75 million dollar loan and up to 300 million dollars in
financing from institutional investors under subscription of
participation agreements with the IDB. 
</P>
