<HEADLINE> Agreement Reached on Lesotho Transitional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 14 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho's ruling party
Lesotho Congress for Democracy (LCD) and the opposition parties
Wednesday reached an agreement on a transitional structure to
oversee preparations for the upcoming elections in the tiny south
African country.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by South African Minister of Safety and
Security Sydney Mufamadi in Lesotho capital Maseru at a press
conference following Wednesday's multi-party talks on the crisis
in the tiny mountain kingdom, South African Press Association
(SAPA) said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Wednesday, the LCD had rejected the establishment of
such a committee, saying that it ran counter to the country's
constitution.
</P>
<P>
The opposition parties had held protests against the results
of the May elections which were allegedly rigged in favor of the
ruling party. 
