<HEADLINE> Romania's Foreign Debt Exceeds 8 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bucharest, October 14 (Xinhua) -- The value of Romania's
foreign debt topped the 8.314 billion U.S. dollars in July.
</P>
<P>
The public debt registered in July was about 4.5 billion
dollars, being 54 percent of the total debt, and the private
commercial debt was 1.8 billion dollars, the national AAApres news
agency quoted the Central Bank as saying.
</P>
<P>
In July, Romania owed the international financial bodies
(International Monetary Fund, European Union, International Bank
for Reconstruction and Development, European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development) about 3.295 billion dollars, out
of which the highest debt, about 44 percent must go to the
International Bank for Reconstruction and Development, and 13.2
percent to the European Union.  
</P>
</TEXT>
